ByChibuike Nwabuko Abuja (Sundiata Post) – The Nigeria’s COVID-19 death toll on Sunday hit 1,002 as the Centre for Disease Control reported 322 new confirmed cases. The report released by the Nigeria Centre for Disease control via its twitter handle has it that the new cases were recorded from 18 states as Lagos, Abuja and FCT came first, second and third with 130, 36 and 25 infections respectively. Others are; Edo-17;  Bayelsa, Ogun and Oyo-14  cases each; Anambra-13; Kaduna-12;  Ondo-11;  Abia-10;  Osun-6; Plateau and Kwara-5 each; Kano-4;  Ebonyi-3; Sokoto-2  and Borno-1 infection. The health agency further informed that the total confirmed COVID-19 cases have risen to 52,227 out of which 38,945 have been discharged. See how the states stand: By Abujah Racheal ABUJA - The Nigeria Centre for Disease Control (NCDC) has announced 653 new COVID-19 cases in the country as total infections from the virus rise to 35, 107. The NCDC made this known on its official twitter handle late on Saturday. The health agency said that as… July 19, 2020 In "Top Stories" The Kano State government has confirmed the death of two more patients who tested positive for coronavirus (COVID-19) in the state. The state Ministry of Health announced this in a tweet, saying that was the situation in Kano as of 12:15pm on Monday. This brings the total number of COVID-19… April 27, 2020 In "Top Stories" By Chibuike Nwabuk Abuja (Sundiata Post) - The reported cases of COVID-19 infections Thursday shrunk to 373 compared to the 473 cases recorded on Wednesday, the Nigeria Centre for Disease Control report has shown. However, there was a reported increase in death toll from 956 the previous day (Wednesday) to… August 14, 2020 In "Top Stories"